description: [U.S. House] Washington, DC -- Today, Congresswomen Sydney Kamlager-Dove (CA-37) and Sara Jacobs (CA-51), Ranking Member of the House Foreign Affairs Subcommittee on Africa, issued the following statement after Donald Trump issued a day-one executive order dissolving the President's Advisory Council on African Diaspora Engagement:
title: Africa: Kamlager-Dove, Jacobs Statement on Trump Administration's Dissolution of Key African Diplomatic Council
